WEBVTT

00:02.569 --> 00:04.799
- Hi, guys.
- Hi, honey.

00:04.871 --> 00:07.396
Well, congratulate me. I got my grades.

00:07.474 --> 00:10.136
4.0 average!

00:10.210 --> 00:13.043
- That's great, honey!
- Great. Alright.

00:13.113 --> 00:16.640
Do you have any idea how
satisfying it is to get straight A's?

00:20.654 --> 00:22.713
Sorry.

00:23.523 --> 00:26.048
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

00:26.126 --> 00:28.686
This last month has been so horrible.

00:28.762 --> 00:33.426
But now, next week,
all I have to do is relax.

00:33.500 --> 00:36.025
That's it. You just
sit back and relax, honey.

00:36.102 --> 00:40.402
Would you get that for me?

00:42.442 --> 00:44.740
Well, heck! Why don't I get it?

00:46.613 --> 00:47.739
Hello?

00:47.814 --> 00:50.510
Yes, colonel, it's me. Yeah.

00:50.584 --> 00:52.916
I'm right here.
You don't have to yell at me.

00:53.620 --> 00:58.387
It's your dad. Uh-huh.
This weekend? Uh-huh.

00:58.491 --> 01:01.324
They have frequent flier mileage
that's gonna expire.

01:01.394 --> 01:06.161
They want to come this weekend.
You... I... What...?

01:06.266 --> 01:08.700
Why don't I let Jill
tell you the good news?

01:11.071 --> 01:12.971
You talk... He's your dad!

01:13.039 --> 01:15.098
Hi, Daddy.

01:15.175 --> 01:20.477
There's nothing that I would like more
than to have you visit, but I'm sick.

01:20.547 --> 01:23.277
Yeah.

01:23.350 --> 01:26.717
Yeah. A head cold.
You know, cough. Flu.

01:26.820 --> 01:29.482
I think I have an ear infection.

01:29.556 --> 01:33.117
Oh, yeah. I'm so sorry.

01:33.193 --> 01:37.129
Oh, well, thank you.
I'm sure I'll feel better soon.

01:37.197 --> 01:39.358
OK. Bye.

01:44.137 --> 01:47.163
- What?
- You lied to Grandpa.

01:47.240 --> 01:51.404
- I didn't exactly lie.
- Well, then what exactly did you do?

01:51.511 --> 01:54.002
There's a very good
explanation for this.

01:54.681 --> 01:56.239
What is it?

01:57.350 --> 02:00.410
I'm really burned out from school.
I need time for myself.

02:00.487 --> 02:04.253
But if I told that to your grandpa,
it would have hurt his feelings.

02:04.357 --> 02:07.656
So when we get older and
we don't want you to visit, can we lie?

02:10.597 --> 02:13.088
Randy, when your father and I get older,

02:13.166 --> 02:16.135
you won't have to lie
because you'll want to be around us.

02:16.202 --> 02:19.365
We're gonna be just as cool
as we are right now. Right, Tim?

02:22.509 --> 02:24.443
I'm dyin' here, aren't I?

02:26.746 --> 02:29.010
All you're missing is the headstone.

